Asymmetric cell division safeguards memory CD8 T cell development

This Data set contains 3 Biological replicates of Tcf1+CD62L+ (+ +) and Tcf1-CD62L- (- -) cells induced by:

  • Antibody (Ab)
  • High affinity peptide (gp33)
  • Low affinity peptide (C6)

Reference genome was downoalded via the following link, as described in the Rsubread package users guide. ftp://ftp.ebi.ac.uk/pub/databases/gencode/Gencode_mouse/release_M18/GRCm38.primary_assembly.genome.fa.gz.

setwd("~PathtoData")
library(Rsubread)
Rsubread::buildindex(basename = "mouse_index",reference = "GRCm38.primary_assembly.genome.fa") 

files <-list.files("~PathtoData")
files <- files[grepl(".fastq.gz", files)]
output_names <- paste0(gsub("_R1.fastq.gz", "", files), ".bam")

for(i in 1:length(files)){
  Rsubread::align(index = "mouse_index",readfile1 = files[i],type = "rna",input_format = "gzFASTQ" ,output_file = output_names[i]) 
}

Production of count matrices

bam_files <- c("1_AB_++.bam", "2_AB_++.bam", "3_AB_++.bam", "1_AB_--.bam", "2_AB_--.bam", "3_AB_--.bam",
               "1_C6_++.bam", "2_C6_++.bam", "3_C6_++.bam", "1_C6_--.bam", "2_C6_--.bam", "3_C6_--.bam",
               "1_gp33_++.bam", "2_gp33_++.bam", "3_gp33_++.bam","1_gp33_--.bam","2_gp33_--.bam", "3_gp33_--.bam")

count_matrices <- Rsubread::featureCounts(files = bam_files, annot.inbuilt = "mm10", useMetaFeatures = TRUE, isPairedEnd=FALSE, strandSpecific = 0)

saveRDS(count_matrices,file="count_matrices.rds")

Creating DGEList object and annotating the genes by using the corresponding NCBI Entrez IDs. Genes are filtered and normalized as recommended in the edgeR Users Guide.

#Creating DGEList object
y_data <-  DGEList(counts=count_matrices[[1]], group=targets$Group)
colnames(y_data) <- names
colnames(y_data) <- gsub(".bam", "", colnames(y_data))

#Annotating genes
require(org.Mm.eg.db)
Symbol <- mapIds(org.Mm.eg.db, keys=rownames(y_data), keytype="ENTREZID", column="SYMBOL")
y_data$genes <- data.frame(Symbol=Symbol)

#Filtering and Normalizing
keep <- filterByExpr(y_data)
y_data <- y_data[keep, ,keep.lib.sizes=FALSE]
y_data <- calcNormFactors(y_data)

library(ggplot2)

logcpm <- cpm(y_data,prior.count = 2,log=TRUE)

genes <- c("Sell", "Tcf7", "Gzmb", "Gzma", "Tbx21", "Ezh2", "IL2rb", "Tnf", "Prdm1", "Id3", "Pdcd1", "Tim3", "Ctla4", "Bcl6", "Bcl2")

for (j in 1:length(unique(Group))) {

}

design <- model.matrix(~0 + Group) 
colnames(design) <- levels(Group)
y_data <- estimateDisp(y_data, design, robust = T)
fit <- glmQLFit(y_data, design)
head(fit$coefficients)
##             AB.--      AB.++      C6.--      C6.++    gp33.--    gp33.++
## 27395   -9.892452 -10.015429  -9.909596 -10.244270  -9.992774 -10.479125
## 18777   -9.362345  -9.580568  -9.599605  -9.789086  -9.729711  -9.911353
## 21399  -10.390696 -10.423467 -10.388074 -10.438911 -10.411658 -10.509496
## 108664 -10.192622 -10.254327 -10.298728 -10.273266 -10.570217 -10.487971
## 12421  -10.942302 -10.558504 -11.151903 -10.600495 -11.083796 -10.626972
## 319263 -10.569092 -10.332574 -10.674841 -10.293965 -10.453710 -10.322932
comparisons <- c(12,34,56)
QLFs <- list()
DEG <- list()
Volcanos <- list()

sign_genes_df <- list()

for (i in 1:length(comparisons)) {
  temp_rep <- rep(0,6)
  temp_comparison <- as.character(comparisons[i])
  temp1 <- as.integer(substring(temp_comparison,first = 1,last = 1))
  temp2 <- as.integer(substring(temp_comparison,first = 2,last = 2))
  temp_rep[temp1] <- -1
  temp_rep[temp2] <- +1
  
  
  QLFs[[i]] <- glmQLFTest(fit, contrast=temp_rep)
  colnames(QLFs[[i]]$coefficients) <- gsub("++", "CD62L+TCF1+", colnames(QLFs[[i]]$coefficients), fixed = TRUE)
  colnames(QLFs[[i]]$coefficients) <- gsub("--", "CD62L-TCF1-", colnames(QLFs[[i]]$coefficients), fixed = TRUE)
  pos.coef <- colnames(QLFs[[i]]$coefficients)[temp_rep == 1]
  neg.coef <- colnames(QLFs[[i]]$coefficients)[temp_rep == -1]
  DEG[[i]] <- topTags(QLFs[[i]], nrow(QLFs[[i]]$table))
  
  DEG[[i]]$table<- subset(DEG[[i]]$table, str_detect(DEG[[i]]$table$Symbol, "(^Rpl)|(^Mrpl)|(^Mt-)|(^Rps)") != F)
  
  DEG[[i]]$table$minus.log10p <- -log10(DEG[[i]]$table$PValue)
  DEG[[i]]$table$minus.log10p[which(DEG[[i]]$table$minus.log10p == Inf)] <-
    DEG[[i]]$table$minus.log10p[which(sort(DEG[[i]]$table$minus.log10p, decreasing =T) != Inf)[1]]+100 #calculating -log10p and setting the ones that are Inf to defined value
  
  
  table <- DEG[[i]]$table
  
  sign_df <- subset(table, abs(logFC) > 1.2 & PValue < 10e-6)
  label.genes <- sign_df$Symbol[which(sign_df$Symbol%in%genes)]

  sign_df$new <-sign_df$Symbol
  sign_df$new[which(sign_df$logFC>0)] <- paste0(sign_df$new[which(sign_df$logFC>0)], "+FC")
  sign_df$new[which(sign_df$logFC<0)] <- paste0(sign_df$new[which(sign_df$logFC<0)], "-FC")
  sign_df <- sign_df[order(sign_df$logFC, decreasing = T),]
  sign_genes_df[[i]] <- as.data.frame(sign_df$new)
  
  
  Volcanos[[i]] <- ggplot2::ggplot(table, aes(x=logFC, y=minus.log10p, label = Symbol)) + geom_point(colour="darkgray") + ggplot2::geom_point(data = subset(table, logFC > 1.2 & PValue < 10e-6), col= "#993895")+ ggplot2::geom_point(data = subset(table, logFC < (-1.2) & PValue < 10e-6), col= "#000000") + ggrepel::geom_text_repel(data =subset(table, Symbol%in%label.genes),  color = 'black', hjust = 0, direction = "y", max.overlaps = Inf, min.segment.length = unit(0.01, 'lines'), force = 1, nudge_y = 5, nudge_x = 1,  box.padding = unit(0.7, "lines")) +
          ggplot2::theme_bw() + ggplot2::ylab("-log10(PValue)") + ggplot2::ggtitle(paste(neg.coef , "(up=-FC)", "vs.", pos.coef, "(up=+FC)"))
}

plot_grid(plotlist = Volcanos, ncol = 1)

pathway_MSig <- msigdbr::msigdbr(species = "Mus musculus", category= "C7")
pathway_MSig <-  split(x = pathway_MSig$gene_symbol, f = pathway_MSig$gs_name)

sets <- c("KAECH_DAY8_EFF_VS_MEMORY_CD8_TCELL_DN", "KAECH_DAY8_EFF_VS_MEMORY_CD8_TCELL_UP")

my_gene_sets <- subset(pathway_MSig, names(pathway_MSig)%in%sets)

GSEA_plots <- list()

for (i in 1:length(QLFs)) {
  df <- QLFs[[i]]$table
  df$Symbol <- QLFs[[i]]$genes$Symbol

  df %>% dplyr::filter(PValue<10e6)%>% dplyr::select("Symbol","logFC")%>% stats::na.omit()%>%dplyr::arrange(-logFC)%>% dplyr::distinct(Symbol, .keep_all = TRUE)-> df_ranked
  df_ranked <- tibble::deframe(df_ranked)
  
  fgsea_res <- fgsea::fgseaMultilevel(pathways=my_gene_sets, stats=df_ranked, minSize=2, maxSize=500, nPermSimple = 10000)
  
  nes <- round(fgsea_res$NES, digits = 3)
  pval <- fgsea_res$pval
  
  plots <- list()
  for (j in 1:length(my_gene_sets)) {
    plots[[j]] <- fgsea::plotEnrichment(my_gene_sets[[j]], df_ranked) + ggplot2::labs(title=paste0(names(my_gene_sets)[j]))
  }
  
  GSEA_plots[[i]] <- plot_grid(plotlist = plots, ncol = 2)
  
}

plot_grid(plotlist = GSEA_plots, ncol = 1)
